body:
We have plans to build a better general system for customizing the style of the notebook.  But that is outside the scope of this PR and the 1.0 release.

@Carreau has a good point.  We need to make our CSS styles part of the notebook format.  People are already putting custom styles in their notebook in this exact manner (even in books!)  All of those things will break if we rename classes, add new classes, remove classes.  Can someone add this to the topic list for the dev meeting?  

But I don't think that should stall this PR.
